{{Italic title}} '''''Creating Masculinity in Los Angeles's Little Manila: Working-Class Filipinos and Popular Culture, 1920s-1950s''''' is a 2006 [[non-fiction book]] authored by Linda España-Maram. It was published by [[Columbia University Press]].<ref name="Samponaro2007">{{cite journal|last1=Samponaro|first1=Philip|title=Creating Masculinity in Los Angeles's Little Manila: Working-Class Filipinos and Popular Culture, 1920s?1950s|journal=The Journal of Popular Culture|volume=40|issue=3|year=2007|pages=575–577|issn=0022-3840|doi=10.1111/j.1540-5931.2007.00420.x}}</ref><ref name="Posadas2007">{{cite journal|last1=Posadas|first1=B. M.|title=Creating Masculinity in Los Angeles's Little Manila: Working-Class Filipinos and Popular Culture, 1920s-1950s|journal=Journal of American History|volume=93|issue=4|year=2007|page=1322|issn=0021-8723|doi=10.2307/25094748}}</ref><ref name="Bonus2008">{{cite journal|last1=Bonus|first1=Rick|title=Book Review: España-Maram, L. (2006). Creating Masculinity in Los Angeles's Little Manila: Working-Class Filipinos and Popular Culture, 1920s-1950s. New York: Columbia University Press|journal=Men and Masculinities|volume=10|issue=5|year=2008|pages=636–638|issn=1097-184X|doi=10.1177/1097184X06299040}}</ref>
